{{Infobox book series | name = Complete Collection of Russian Chronicles | image = Nikon letopis 1.jpg | image_caption = | books = | author = [[Archaeographical Commission]] | title_orig = Полное собрание русских летописей | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = [[Russia]], [[Soviet Union]] | language = [[Russian language|Russian]] | genre = history | publisher = Typography of Edward Prats | pub_date = 1841 | english_pub_date = | media_type = | number_of_books = 43 volumes | list_books = | preceded by = | followed by = }}
The '''Complete Collection of Russian Chronicles''' ({{Lang-ru|Полное собрание русских летописей|translit=Polnoe Sobranie Russkikh Letopisey}}, abbr. ''PSRL'') is a series of published volumes aimed at collecting all medieval [[East Slavic languages|East Slavic]] chronicles, with various editions published in [[Imperial Russia]], the [[Soviet Union]], and [[Russian Federation]]. The project is ongoing and far from finished.
The chronicles were assembled by the [[Archaeographical Expedition]] of the [[Russian Academy of Sciences]] (starting in 1828). They were prepared for publication by the [[Archaeographical Commission]], established in 1834 as part of the [[Ministry of National Education (Russian Empire)|Ministry of National Enlightenment]]. The first volumes were published by a publisher "Typography of Edward Prats". The commission was charged to publish the collection on February 18, 1837.
The first ten volumes appeared between 1841 and 1863. New volumes have been brought forth piecemeal throughout the 20th and early 21st centuries. Some of the older volumes have also been reprinted, especially after 1997.
==List of published volumes== ===Typography of Edward Prats=== * Volume 1. ''[[Laurentian Codex|Laurentian]] and Trinitarian Codices.'' Saint Petersburg, 1846 * Volume 2. ''[[Hypatian Codex]].'' Saint Petersburg, 1843 (included also Hustynian Chronicle) * Volume 3. ''[[Novgorod First Chronicle|Novgorodian Codex]].'' Saint Petersburg, 1841 * Volume 4. ''[[Novgorod Fourth Chronicle|Chronicles of Novgorod and Pskov]].'' Saint Petersburg, 1848 * Volume 5. ''Chronicles of Pskov and Sophia.'' Saint Petersburg, 1851 * Volume 6. ''[[Sofia First Chronicle|Sofia Chronicle]].'' Saint Petersburg, 1853 * Volume 7. ''Chronicle of Resurrection List.'' Saint Petersburg, 1856 * Volume 8. ''Continuation of the Resurrection List Chronicle.'' Saint Petersburg, 1859 * Volume 9. ''[[Nikon Chronicle|Chronicles collection named as Patriarchal or Nikon Chronicle]].'' Saint Petersburg, 1862 * Number of indices (1868-1907)
In 1871-72 the first two volumes were republished as the second editions.
===Typography of Skorokhodov and Typography of Aleksandrov===
